    {
      "name": "Shadow Slip",
      "type": "feat",
      "data": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Shadrix becomes an inky cloud of shadow and can move up to half his flying speed without provoking opportunity attacks, then resumes his true form. During this movement, he can move through creatures and objects as if they were difficult terrain. If he moves through a creature, it must succeed on a DC <span class=\"rd__dc\">21</span> Constitution saving throw or become @condition[blinded] until the end of its next turn. If Shadrix ends this move inside an object, he takes 5 ([[/r 1d10]]) force damage and is shunted to the nearest unoccupied space.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>",
